      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR SHERALEE (1) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 342m at this track two runs back then settled forward again when finishing second at this track last start. Has good early burn and is suited drawn on the inside. Must come into calculations. CHRISTOFF (2) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when third (20.51) at this track. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Must be included in calculations. SMOOTH PARADISE (5) has mixed form recently, finishing fourth (20.56) in a Other at this track latest but did run well two back when in the frame. Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break off the middle. Expected to bounce back to best. DISTRICTS DUB (7) is in the mix despite finishing out of the placings here last start.",
